[
    {
        "content": "<p>Trivial issue of the day: in mathlib, bundled versions of the map <code>fun v ↦ k • v</code> (with fixed <code>k</code>, and <code>v</code> as the argument) are sometimes called <code>smulLeft</code> and sometimes <code>smulRight</code>!</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">DivisionRing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">AddCommGroup</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">AddMonoidHom</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">smulLeft</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">•</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Equiv</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">smulRight</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">•</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I spotted this because I wanted to make an <code>AddEquiv</code> version (it would have saved a line or two in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/29914\">#29914</a>), which would have extended both <code>AddMonoidHom.smulLeft</code> and <code>Equiv.smulRight</code>, and I couldn't work out what to call it.</p>\n<p>I think <code>Equiv.smulRight</code> is the one that's wrong here, and should become <code>Equiv.smulLeft</code>. Is this worth fixing, or should we leave it be (and tolerate the naming inconsistency) for the sake of not breaking existing code?</p>",
        "id": 543323424,
        "sender_full_name": "David Loeffler",
        "timestamp": 1759759205
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is the equiv version <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=DistribMulAction.toAddAut#doc\">docs#DistribMulAction.toAddAut</a> ?</p>",
        "id": 543324614,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1759759434
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Equiv.smulRight</code> is really just <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=MulAction.toPerm#doc\">docs#MulAction.toPerm</a> combined with <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Units.mk0#doc\">docs#Units.mk0</a></p>",
        "id": 543324953,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1759759509
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>arguably <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=AddMonoidHom.smulLeft#doc\">docs#AddMonoidHom.smulLeft</a> should just be deleted, it's just an alias of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=DistribMulAction.toAddMonoidHom#doc\">docs#DistribMulAction.toAddMonoidHom</a></p>",
        "id": 543325238,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1759759574
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"310045\">Eric Wieser</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Naming.20discrepancy.3A.20.60smulLeft.60.20vs.20.60smulRight.60/near/543324614\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is the equiv version <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=DistribMulAction.toAddAut#doc\">docs#DistribMulAction.toAddAut</a> ?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Not quite, since <code>K</code> isn't a group, only a <code>GroupWithZero</code> (and we don't have a concept of <code>DistribMulActionWithZero</code>).</p>",
        "id": 543325553,
        "sender_full_name": "David Loeffler",
        "timestamp": 1759759645
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"310045\">Eric Wieser</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Naming.20discrepancy.3A.20.60smulLeft.60.20vs.20.60smulRight.60/near/543325238\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>arguably <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=AddMonoidHom.smulLeft#doc\">docs#AddMonoidHom.smulLeft</a> should just be deleted, it's just an alias of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=DistribMulAction.toAddMonoidHom#doc\">docs#DistribMulAction.toAddMonoidHom</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Maybe, but we also have e.g. <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=ContinuousLinearEquiv.smulLeft#doc\">docs#ContinuousLinearEquiv.smulLeft</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=OrderIso.mulLeft#doc\">docs#OrderIso.mulLeft</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=LinearMap.mulLeft#doc\">docs#LinearMap.mulLeft</a>, etc.</p>",
        "id": 543326649,
        "sender_full_name": "David Loeffler",
        "timestamp": 1759759897
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>DistribMulAction.toAddEquiv (Units.mk0 v hv)</code> would presumably suffice for the <code>GroupWithZero</code> case</p>",
        "id": 543330128,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1759760658
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess we could add shorthands for each of these <code>Units.mk0</code> versions by appending a <code>\\0</code> to the other name</p>",
        "id": 543330397,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1759760721
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That is indeed is a very elegant way of implementing it. But I think you are not appreciating quite how utterly trivial my question is here:  <em>What should it be called</em>? <span aria-label=\"slight smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f642\" role=\"img\" title=\"slight smile\">:slight_smile:</span> </p>\n<p>Should it be <code>AddEquiv.smulLeft₀</code> (consistently with <code>AddMonoidHom.smulLeft</code>), or <code>AddEquiv.smulRight₀</code> (consistently with <code>Equiv.smulRight</code>)?</p>",
        "id": 543332580,
        "sender_full_name": "David Loeffler",
        "timestamp": 1759761201
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I claim it should be called <code>DistribMulAction.toAddEquiv₀</code></p>",
        "id": 543338210,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1759762455
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Either that or we should rename the entire family of <code>DistribMulAction.toAddEquiv</code> declarations, of which I would guess there are 10-20:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=MulAction.toEndHom#doc\">docs#MulAction.toEndHom</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=MulAction.toPerm#doc\">docs#MulAction.toPerm</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=MulAction.toPermHom#doc\">docs#MulAction.toPermHom</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=DistribMulAction.toAddMonoidHom#doc\">docs#DistribMulAction.toAddMonoidHom</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=DistribMulAction.toAddMonoidEnd#doc\">docs#DistribMulAction.toAddMonoidEnd</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=DistribMulAction.toAddEquiv#doc\">docs#DistribMulAction.toAddEquiv</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=DistribMulAction.toAddAut#doc\">docs#DistribMulAction.toAddAut</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=DistribMulAction.toLinearMap#doc\">docs#DistribMulAction.toLinearMap</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=DistribMulAction.toModuleEnd#doc\">docs#DistribMulAction.toModuleEnd</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=DistribMulAction.toLinearEquiv#doc\">docs#DistribMulAction.toLinearEquiv</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=DistribMulAction.toModuleAut#doc\">docs#DistribMulAction.toModuleAut</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Module.toModuleEnd#doc\">docs#Module.toModuleEnd</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Algebra.lsmul#doc\">docs#Algebra.lsmul</a> (refers to the pattern in the docstring)</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 543338429,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1759762509
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hmm...  that's a lot of renaming to no clear benefit; I was just trying to resolve the left-right ambiguity, not anything beyond that. </p>\n<p>How about the following proposal?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>create <code>DistribMulAction.toAddEquiv₀</code>, but also make <code>AddEquiv.smulLeft₀</code> an alias for it</li>\n<li>rename the existing <code>Equiv.smulRight</code> to <code>Equiv.smulLeft₀</code> (deprecating the old name as usual)?</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 543340999,
        "sender_full_name": "David Loeffler",
        "timestamp": 1759763022
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Perhaps those should be changed to <code>alias</code>es too?</p>",
        "id": 543347565,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1759764329
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"310045\">Eric Wieser</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Naming.20discrepancy.3A.20.60smulLeft.60.20vs.20.60smulRight.60/near/543347565\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Perhaps those should be changed to <code>alias</code>es too?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Which ones? Do you mean that we should have<code>MulAction.toPerm₀</code>, and <code>Equiv.smulLeft₀</code> should be an alias for it?</p>",
        "id": 543350520,
        "sender_full_name": "David Loeffler",
        "timestamp": 1759764870
    }
]